# Fix: PyTorch 2.6 changed torch.load default to weights_only=True.
# BatchEncoding (transformers) is not in the allowed globals list, so cached
# testloader/dataloader files produced with earlier PyTorch versions crash on
# load unless weights_only=False is explicit.
#
# Applied to: all 4 torch.load() call sites in main.py
#   - line ~99:  testloader (eval path)
#   - line ~329: dataloader (calibration path)
#   - line ~343: act_scales (LET path)
#   - line ~344: act_shifts (LET path)
#
# Affected arms: C and D (fresh python main.py invocations see the patched file)
# Arms A and B: calibration was already in-flight when crash occurred;
#               use scripts/run_omniquant_rerun_AB.sh to re-run them.
